

Ex:
POST /login HTTP/1.1
Host: 0a1900770431fc28c06002f900a200d0.web-security-academy.net
Cookie: session=ATVicWTMEAwb8mjcpqofvtHmSrP4dn6L; 
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (X11; Linux x86_64; rv:102.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/102.0

csrf=fL0rS2Vz1uIDBLtAptQB1gyRnsagNa5v&username=wiener&password=peter

When you see an action that makes important changes, see if you find csrf variable. Usually will be in POST forms. If not present, check if it is vulnerable to csrf.

Check other steps in 'hacktricks' and 'payloadallthethings'.

